[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST obviously has to pass when NORTH opens 1\S.

WEST has a reasonable Takeout Double. She hopes EAST will name a suit and they can just 
play a partscore.

You should almost always bid when partner makes a Takeout Double. Almost always. This is the one time 
when you don't. EAST's \S are so good that he passes, converting the Takeout Double into a 
Penalty Double.}

